.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B RCLONEFZF_HISTORY
Path to the rclonefzf history file.

If the environment variable
.B RCLONEFZF_HISTORY
is defined, it will be used directly.

Otherwise, rclonefzf determines the history file path using the first
available value in the following order:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B $XDG_CACHE_HOME/rclonefzf/rclonefzf_history
.IP \(bu 2
.B $HOME/.cache/rclonefzf/rclonefzf_history
.IP \(bu 2
.B ~/.cache/rclonefzf/rclonefzf_history

.PP
If
.B RCLONEFZF_HISTORY
is set to any of the following values, history will be disabled and
no history file will be written:
.IP \(bu 2
.B false
.IP \(bu 2
.B False
.IP \(bu 2
.B no
.IP \(bu 2
.B No
.RE

.TP
.B RCLONEFZF_PREVIEW_WINDOW
Controls the layout and size of the fzf preview window.

The value is passed directly to fzfâ€™s
.BR --preview-window
option.

Default:
.RS
.B bottom,43%,border-double
.RE

.TP
.B NO_COLOR
Disable all ANSI color output.

When set, rclonefzf disables:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
fzf color themes
.IP \(bu 2
ANSI color output in messages

.PP
This follows the
.B NO_COLOR
convention used by many CLI tools.
.RE

.TP
.B NO_FX
Disable terminal effects.

When set, rclonefzf will not use terminal title save and restore
sequences.


